[UTCDate "2019.04.16"]
[UTCTime "22:24:10"]
[ChapterMode "gamebook"]

{ The question of how a chess player comes to a certain move has been studied before. You can find a nice book by Jeremy Silman called, "The Amateur's Mind" where he observes players of various skill solving the same chess positions. There are also a wide range of studies done regarding the selection process.

This study was created so you don't have to sift through the mass of studies - some still locked behind paywalls or only barely accessible. Each chapter of this study has a position to solve from Akiba Rubinstein's historic games. The full games are located at the end of the study if you wish to further study them. Some chapters are oriented to free study, while others are meant to walk you through a process. Enjoy! }
 *


